						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1470 (1549 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged and party built in. Seems to record a gift of some land out of the <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> village Mēlppākkam in Śōḻaśiṅgapurappaṟṟu by Kandāḍai Appaṅgār, son of Tōḻappar, the <hi rend="italic">āchārya</hi> of •••• dēvarāja. The details of the date viz. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1470, Kīlaka, Mīṉa ba. 10, Friday correspond to 1549, A.D. March 23, Saturday, not Friday.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
